SIMPLE: effrontery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Effrontery
<hw>Ef*front"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Effronteries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>effronterie</ets>, fr. <ets>effront⟦eacute⟧</ets> shameless, fr. L.
<ets>effrons</ets>, <ets>-ontis</ets>, putting forth the forehead,
<it>i. e.</it>, barefaced, shameless; <ets>ex</ets> + <ets>frons</ets>
the forehead. See <er>Front</er>.]</ety> <def>Impudence or boldness in
confronting or in transgressing the bounds of duty or decorum; insulting
presumptuousness; shameless boldness; barefaced assurance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Corruption lost nothing of its <qex>effrontery</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Impudence; sauciness. See
<er>Impudence</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effrontit</ent>⟦br⟧
